question: if you’re taking prompts you should write an ambris tyrus sleepover like i said uwu
answer:
This turned out as less sleepover and more double date but please take it anyway I tried.

TJ and Amber jogged downstairs at the sound of the doorbell ringing merrily. TJ swung the door open to reveal his boyfriend and Amber’s girlfriend, grinning on their porch.

“Hey, babe,” TJ greeted, leaning forward to kiss Cyrus as Amber stepped aside so Cyrus and Iris could step into the house. They filed inside, inhaling deeply at the warm scent of cinnamon and sugar filling the house. They glanced around, smiling at the family photos on the walls, spanning all 16 years of TJ and Amber’s life.

“Happy Halloween eve!” Iris exclaimed as they took off their coats, hanging them up by the door and toeing off their shoes.

“Is that actually a thing?” TJ asked incredulously, looking over his shoulder as he led the other three into the kitchen, gesturing for them to leave their bags on the couch as the passed.

“I don’t think so,” Cyrus jumped in with a chuckle, setting his bag down. “But we can still call it that!”

“Good plan,” Amber replied with a smile, following TJ into the kitchen and standing on one side of the island next to him. Cyrus and Iris stood across from them, looking a little confused.

“What exactly are we doing?” Iris asked, looking around the kitchen.

“We’re making pumpkin pie!” TJ exclaimed, looking as if his answer was the most obvious one possible.

“Aren’t we like a month early?” Cyrus asked, torn between teasing and genuine confusion. TJ shrugged, opening cabinets and pulling out ingredients.

“I mean probably, but we had pumkin anyway, and I didn’t want to go to the store,” he replied, setting a can of pumpkin puree on the island as emphasis.

“My boyfriend, ladies and gentlemen,” Cyrus turned to Iris and pretended to swoon, holding the back of his hand to his forehead. “Such a romantic he is.”

“Yes, truly,” Amber replied, teasing her twin brother gently.

“You two are terrible,” TJ said, laughing. “Iris, save me.”

“I can only try.”

“Alright, pie is baking, and now we wait,” Amber said as she closed the oven door, turning back to the other three.

“What do we do in the meantime?” Cyrus asked. TJ looked at his boyfriend, then himself. A quick glance at the other two confirmed his suspicions, and he bit back a giggle at the sight of the four of them, covered in flour and pumpkin puree.

“We should probably get cleaned up,” he laughed, gesturing to their state. “Cy, you managed to get pie crust in your hair,” he said, reaching forward to pull the crust from his boyfriend’s soft brown hair.

“Well you have pie filling all over your face,” Cyrus retorted, gently swiping his thumb across TJ’s cheek to clean away the orange filling.

“They’re adorable,” Iris whispered to her girlfriend, watching TJ and Cyrus stare into each other’s eyes.

“So are we,” Amber argued warmly, resting her head on Iris’s shoulder as they leaned against the counter.

“It’s not a competition, Ambs.”

“I know that!” Amber insisted. “But if it were…”

“We’d win.”

summary:
Day 12. Least Favorite Character?
Definitley either Morgan or Miranda. I GUESS I have to cut Morgan a liiiittle slack because...
body:
Day 12. Least Favorite Character?

Definitley either Morgan or Miranda. I GUESS I have to cut Morgan a liiiittle slack because she’s 7, but. Yikes. I really do not like her, and Miranda is definitley no better. In fact, she’s probably even worse because she was supposed to be the adult in that situation. The scene where Bowie breaks up with Miranda was probably one of my favorite scenes that episode. Past the obvious lying and manipulating of Miranda’s character, I just…don’t really see any redeeming qualities? It’s probably because she’s a supporting role and she was only brought in to cause obsticals for Bexie narratively, but still, I don’t see much in her besides her bad side. Like, her good side is sort of…boring.

If you meant least favorite main character, I guess I’d have to give that one to Jonah? I do like Jonah, I just don’t think we really saw much growth or development from him until his anxiety arc, and even then, it’s very small. Like, his entire personality, or the one thing that’s constant with his character at least, seems to center around frisbee. And maybe Andi. But, like I said, I do like him! It’s just, if I had to pick a least favorite main character, it would probably have to go to him.

summary: There’s some changes to Disney Channel’s schedule for next week, October 15-21. Changes include more reruns of Bizaardvark,...
caption:
There’s some changes to Disney Channel’s schedule for next week, October 15-21. Changes include more reruns of Bizaardvark, Stuck in the Middle, resulting in K.C. Undercover, Austin & Ally and Liv and Maddie reruns being removed from the schedule. There’s slightly less reruns of Bunk’d and Jessie airing this week. Tuesday 10/16 sees DuckTales, Big City Greens, and Gravity Falls move from 1-2:30 PM ET to 2-3:30 PM ET. 

Once Again. there’s new episodes of Andi Mack, Coop & Cami Ask the World, the Season 2 Premiere of DuckTales, new Hotel Transylvania: The Series, Fancy Nancy, Mickey Mouse, Mickey and the Roadster Racers, Puppy Dog Pals, Raven’s Home and Star Wars Resistance.
